historical development and policy objectives. Except for Québec, all other Canadian jurisdictions now 
consider CDR recommendations when making their own decisions. Decision criteria and methods vary 
(see Box 3). Generally, formulary decisions are made by the respective provincial or territorial Ministry of 
Health based on the recommendations of a committee. 59. 
