predominant in formulary decisions or explicitly outlined in decision-making criteria. What is meant by 
economic considerations ranges from simple budget impact analysis to more elaborate cost-effectiveness 
studies provided by the manufacturer. Pharmaco-economic assessment has been formally taken into 
account in reimbursement decisions for several years in Ontario and British Columbia. However, no 23 
