2006c). Using IMS data, the PMPRB compared ex-factory prices of generics and other non-patented drugs DELSA/HEA/WD/HWP(2006)4 74 using  " average foreign-to-Canadian prices ratios "  (arithmetic mean). In bilateral comparisons, generic 
prices were found to be systematically lower in foreign countries 91 than in Canada. On a bilateral 
comparison, Canada's prices for generics exceeded those in each of the 11 comparison countries. Canadian 
prices for non-patented drugs also exceeded those in all comparator countries except Switzerland and the 
